Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.99,0:00:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The most crucial moment in life is during decision making.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.95,0:00:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The Pacific War taught us the preciousness of peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.03,0:00:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,But also instilled \Nnumerous lessons on how to live.{unsure, lit is "for the sake of living, precepts, numerous left behind"}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.38,0:00:31.59,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,700)\c&H0007DF&\fs100\b1\bord0\blur1}Animentary\N{\b\c&HE0DBF3&}Decision
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.21,0:00:43.33,Default,,0,0,30,,Wit is your weapon{honestly no clue what is megurase here, deepl says "rack one's brain"}\NRemember to use your head{智恵をめぐらせ 頭を使え}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.33,0:00:50.95,Default,,0,0,30,,Repress your anguish, \NIf you are a man{悩み抜け抜け 男なら}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.95,0:00:58.86,Default,,0,0,30,,One decision is enough \NTo make others cry or laugh{泣くも笑うも 決断ひとつ}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.86,0:01:06.69,Default,,0,0,30,,If you win, don't hold your head high, \NIf you lose, don't cry{勝っておごるな 敗れて泣くな}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.69,0:01:14.55,Default,,0,0,30,,Men, don't you ever let others see your tears{男 涙は見せぬもの}
Comment: 0,0:01:34.91,0:01:34.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{ch}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.72,0:01:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason the war in the Pacific started was because of Japan's southern strategy to acquire oil deposits.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.76,0:01:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Planning to cross the seas \Nand land right on the enemy's heads, this operation
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.67,0:01:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,was truly unprecedented in its scale \Nin the worldwide history of warfare.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.02,0:02:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,For that operation, Lieutenant General Imamura \Nreceived under his command various task forces -
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.54,0:02:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,land, naval, aerial - each branch of the Japanese military \Njoined his 16th Army.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.93,0:02:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,A large-scale combined operation was started.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.00,0:02:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,On January 2, 1942, \NJapanese troops occupied the Filipino capital of Manila.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.26,0:02:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Harnessing that momentum, \Nthey turned their eye to the east of Borneo,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.28,0:02:25.37,Default,,0,0,0,,where just across the Makassar Strait, \Nthe island of Celebes was targeted for the next operation. {/the operation of capturing ... was unfolding/expanding}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.08,0:02:30.29,Default,,0,0,0,,As part of this Celebes Island operation,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.29,0:02:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the Southern Detachment of the Navy \Ndrew up a plan for an attack with paratroopers.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.62,0:02:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Overseeing the preparations was Vice Admiral Tsukahara, \NCommander-in-Chief of the 11th Air Fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.20,0:02:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Our main body of several thousand troops \Nwill head to Manado on the west coast. {honestly, unsure about this whole sentence}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.53,0:02:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But some detachments \Nwould also land in Kema from the east.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.00,0:02:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll squeeze the enemy from both sides. {attack on both sides; pincer movement; double envelopment}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.19,0:02:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,At the same time, the paratrooper battalion \Nlands in Langoan,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.92,0:02:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,so as to capture Langoan's air base \Nand the freshwater supply in Kakas.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.68,0:03:03.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you suggesting we paradrop the troops \Nright on the enemy positions? {right in the center (centre)​}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.25,0:03:07.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy would be distracted, softened up for them. \NHe, who makes the first move, wins. {lit: "... that power would be weakened, victory goes to the one who makes the first move; being quick to take action leads to victory; the early bird gets the worm​"}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.42,0:03:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,For the Japanese navy paratrooper corps, \Nbeing in the lead for this operation {maybe "paramarines"}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.05,0:03:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,meant announcing themselves to a world \Nthey were unfamiliar with.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.15,0:03:41.83,Sign,,0,0,260,,{\c&HE9E9E9&\b1\blur1\bord0\xshad7\yshad1\4c&HABA09D&\4a&H62&}Episode 10 \N {\fs100} The Navy Paratrooper Corps
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.73,0:03:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's win first, before making any more plans. {absolutely no clue what he means to say by "the victory in a fight is deciding first; settling (a matter) first; first priority"}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.63,0:04:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I know it's well planned out, but still, isn't it too reckless \Nto just drop the paratroopers right on the enemy's heads? {/in the middle of enemy encampment}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.60,0:04:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The mission of holding out in a pocket
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.49,0:04:07.99,Default,,0,0,0,,would be extremely dangerous \Nfor our paratrooper battalion with so few troops. {very unsure what he means: daily, facing/meeting enemy besiegement/encirclement, with so little force of ... is ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.58,0:04:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I am fully aware of the risks.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.66,0:04:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Please reconsider their drop zone.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.44,0:04:18.95,Default,,0,0,0,,My unit doesn't fear death. \NBut seeing to it that their lives aren't wasted... {no clue what he means "only/just best of the bestest/ideal utmost"; also would assume he is some commander (although not active participant) of the paratroopers, otherwise why'd he be speaking on their behalf?}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.71,0:04:24.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It's already decided that capturing Celebes with the forces of the paratrooper battalion is the best plan. {/best/ideal}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.95,0:04:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But it is still possible to change the drop zone!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.96,0:04:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,What matters now is to decide \Non how to carry out the existing plan. {I hope he means this tho generally unsure: un which way to execute the strategy decided upon}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.32,0:04:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Our current preference is this strategy. {preference; priority; precedence} {again, unsure why he adds sakusen here}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.43,0:04:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing but that! {I have no clue who are those two btw}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.76,0:04:40.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The value of paradrop tactics \Nis in catching the enemy by surprise,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.25,0:04:45.64,Default,,0,0,0,,thus seizing the initiative at a moment's notice. \NSuch has been proven in this war by countries like Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.14,0:04:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Inspired by their successes, the Japanese navy \Nalso gave birth to their own paratroopers corps in 1941.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.55,0:04:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,While maintaining secrecy, the men comprising it \Nwere put through life-threatening drills.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.38,0:05:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,While the navy paratroopers were starting their descent \Nat 4 a.m., January 11th of 1942,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.48,0:05:07.05,Default,,0,0,0,,a coordinated naval landing right in the face of the enemy
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.05,0:05:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,was commenced both from the eastern \Nand the western coasts of Celebes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.19,0:06:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry to the airfield!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.69,0:06:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry up to the airfield, before anything else! {/asap}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.11,0:06:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't abandon the paratroopers at the enemy's mercy! {letting (someone) die without helping}\NDon't let the paratroopers get captured! {/imprisoned}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.42,0:06:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Bluer than indigo, \NTo the skies, to the skies! {♪ Sora no Shinpei (The Divine Soldiers of the Sky) - lines copied from https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iu9GoseEhzY}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.44,0:06:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,In an instant, it is full: \NCountless parachutes open up
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.84,0:06:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,What a glorious sight it is, \NLike the bloom of pure white roses!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.24,0:06:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at that! Parachutes are dropping from the sky
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.86,0:06:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at that! Parachutes soar into the sky
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.04,0:07:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at that! The parachutes soar into the sky
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.87,0:07:38.87,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\c&HDEE1EB&\blur1\bord0\pos(385.23,63.96)} Manado
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.87,0:07:38.87,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\c&HDEE1EB&\blur1\bord0\pos(1142.15,531.39)} Kema
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.87,0:07:38.87,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\c&HDEE1EB&\blur1\bord0\pos(986.18,728.24)} Kakas
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.87,0:07:38.87,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\c&HDEE1EB&\blur1\bord0\pos(784,819.81)} Langoan
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.87,0:07:42.75,Default,,0,0,0,,January 12th, 11:30 a.m.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.75,0:07:47.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The ground troops finally managed to link up \Nwith the navy paratroopers.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.99,0:07:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,No more than 31 hour had passed \Nsince the operation started.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.58,0:08:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Murai, you son of a bitch!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.59,0:08:04.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Tateno, you son of a bitch.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.31,0:08:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,That was one damn fine paradrop.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.86,0:08:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,No, all thanks to your guys. \NThat assault was something.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.57,0:08:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't wait until we finally met. {/wanted to meet asap - as if this scene wasn't gay enough as it is}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.46,0:08:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Our guys rushed like hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.08,0:08:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it's been damn ages.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.04,0:08:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Last time, in the military academy... \NWe used to gaze at the sky{ like that} a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.61,0:08:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh. Good times.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.08,0:08:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The success of our paradrop \Nis rightly your success.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.58,0:08:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.89,0:08:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,This was achieved through the close cooperation \Nof both our Special Navy Landing Forces. {marines and paratroopers}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.20,0:08:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Japan's paratroopers experiment \Nyielded a complete success. {/initial trial/attempt}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.03,0:08:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,For that feat alone, the paratroopers were \Nat the time dubbed
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.42,0:09:00.68,Default,,0,0,0,,"The Divine Soldiers from the Sky," \Nand enjoyed quite a following.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.17,0:09:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Paratrooper, swing me! {guess}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.33,0:09:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The paratroopers are all the rage, \Nwherever they go. {important person; influential figure; big shot; big name; bigwig; heavyweight}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.41,0:09:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,These days, they're Divine Soldiers from the Sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.29,0:09:23.79,Default,,0,0,0,,That's because their parachutes are a sight to behold. {/gorgeous}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.79,0:09:25.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, you shouldn't be jealous of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.87,0:09:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not. I know there's nothing to be jealous of.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.64,0:09:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Paratrooper, swing! Please swing me! {still a guess}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.10,0:09:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,This makes the ground troops look like dirt.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.26,0:09:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Aren't we all comrades in arms, \Nsharing the same blood and flesh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.12,0:09:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.28,0:09:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you a paratrooper?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.20,0:09:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh... No, I'm not.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.06,0:09:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,This here is a paratrooper.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.79,0:09:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Paratrooper, you absolutely must tell us about yourself. {unsure what she means, she makes it sound as though she wants it herself}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.92,0:09:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey-hey, drop it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.96,0:09:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I beg you! The children are getting under my skin! {/waiting}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.28,0:09:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not a good teller... {abs. guess, no clue what he means by "if you're weak", was "I am contused." in HA; assumed "I'm weak [at telling stories]" but could think of "I'm weak [after the operation and supposed to get a rest]"}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.42,0:09:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to mind me. \NI know how to be a good sport. {lit is "this is also one of the friendship; goodwill; friendly relations; amity" but I'm not sure what he means, assumed "we're friends/comrades, so we have to be understanding/make concessions"; was "act of goodwill" in HA which also isn't bad}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.29,0:10:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Quicker, quicker!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.89,0:10:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Murai, I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.28,0:10:05.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever, I'm getting pretty used to it anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.18,0:10:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.02,0:10:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Paratroop! Mr. Paratroop, raise me!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.58,0:10:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, come closer.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.76,0:10:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Up you go, kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.16,0:10:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Paratroopers are not doing it alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.97,0:10:44.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The soil of this goddamn Celebes Island \Nis soaked in the blood of our land assault troops as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.61,0:10:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's there?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.98,0:10:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop it! Break it up!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.24,0:10:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,What is your unit?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.42,0:10:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Airborne corps. {空挺部隊}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.76,0:11:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,A paratrooper, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.80,0:11:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I was just... {was "My unit is..." in HA which also seems legit, but later he uses that start to explain his actions}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.70,0:11:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I know already!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.20,0:11:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Return to your unit.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.23,0:11:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Return at once!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.58,0:11:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I was just...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.78,0:11:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,No need. I know exactly how you feel about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.90,0:11:16.75,Default,,0,0,0,,These damn paratroopers are unbearably selfish! {/think they achieved it all by themselves}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.21,0:11:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,They think they captured it all by themselves!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.28,0:11:22.45,Default,,0,0,0,,But when I think of my comrades \Nthat lost their lives here, I can't stand it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.39,0:11:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand. But what do you suppose we do about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.47,0:11:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,If we leave it as it is, \Nboth sides would have to sustain damage. {/only be hurt}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.37,0:11:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't there any way we...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.84,0:11:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Your emotions are no mystery to me. \NBut all we do is just fall from the sky on our parachutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.47,0:11:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,There must be some mistake in the way we do it now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.47,0:11:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,This whole "Divine Soldiers from the Sky" baloney \Ntroubles us just as much.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.31,0:11:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,That's just what I've been telling them. \NBut when I think of my subordinates, I cannot sleep. {no clue what he means by "I won't sit still/patiently/motionlessly }
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.31,0:11:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen, Murai. You're just getting \Nunreasonably anxious over trifles. {/I think you shouldn't to find fault (with trivial matters); to scold over minor things; to get angry over trifles; to raise one's eyebrows}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.01,0:11:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Time will settle this by itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.82,0:11:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.46,0:12:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So you still cannot understand how I feel about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.42,0:12:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.83,0:12:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,we're on the battlefield!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.13,0:12:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We may both get sent \Nto the front line tomorrow already.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.57,0:12:08.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Every single day, we put our lives on the line!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.35,0:12:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We've no time for such things. {no fucking clue what he means by "such thing forever"; was "such a thing..." in HA}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.47,0:12:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait! Murai!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.05,0:12:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,"Divine Soldiers from the Sky?"
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.83,0:12:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this really the hero \Nthat our warring nation craves? {nation at war; militant nation - no clue what he means, again. those dialogues are a fucking inconsequenta fest}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.07,0:12:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Think you're the cream of the crop \Njust cause you're a paratrooper?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.75,0:12:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You prick! Quit pretending there are no other soldiers \Nbut those with parachutes!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.55,0:12:48.85,Default,,0,0,0,,This hero is product of fantasy. {lit is "made hero" would assume "made up"} \NI have nothing but pity for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.09,0:13:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, if we leave things as they are, the chasm between \Nthe two branches will become ridiculously wide!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.70,0:13:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to think of some cure, and fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.07,0:13:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe, it'll have a lasting impact \Non all our operational plans hereafter.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.62,0:13:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The paradrop operation \Nhas been an astounding success.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.46,0:13:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Its few downsides can be safely overlooked! {/don't get hung up on trifles}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.79,0:13:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand. But sir...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.62,0:13:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Battalion commander, the subject is exhausted. \NConcentrate on current operations!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.28,0:13:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.56,0:13:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The operation was successful beyond any expectations, \Nallowing us to hasten the fall of Java by a whole month.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.91,0:13:32.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It was because we we focused on the strategy. {no fucking clue what he means by strategy/operation first principle, DeepL: This is the result of an operations-first mentality.; HA: strategy first; I think he means "we didn't occupy our minds with extra things aside from operation" tho can be anything; it doesn't help that "sakusen" has two meanings either}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.32,0:13:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,This issue doesn't require any immediate decision from us.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.38,0:13:38.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The paratroopers will move on \Nto execute other operations.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.59,0:13:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? The paratroopers corps is being transferred?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.06,0:13:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Apply your mind to the operation, \NBattalion Commander. {/concentrate on}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.06,0:14:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,For about a month more, \Nthe paratroopers were staying on Celebes Island,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.13,0:14:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,until finally, further south, the new battlefields \Nof Timor and Tarpan were calling out to them. {/departed for } {I'm being rarted again but I can't figure out what's this tarpan thing\Nwas "turban" in HA\NMy best bet is that the narrator misread/mispronounced Kupang, because it's クーパン and ターパン are a bit similar}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.56,0:14:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,With the departure of the paratroopers,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.27,0:14:52.29,Default,,0,0,0,,the conflict between the ground forces and the paratroopers \Nseemed to have petered out by itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.85,0:15:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, a few words please. Don't you have \Nsome interesting story about the paratroopers battalion?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.26,0:15:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,How about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.98,0:15:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,While exchanging emotional handshakes with the paratroopers at the Kakas airfield, how did you feel? Do tell.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.96,0:15:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I got nothing! {rather, I felt nothing}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.99,0:15:15.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.70,0:15:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're so obsessed with writing about paratroopers, \Nwhy don't you go ask them directly?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.33,0:15:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's restrain from violence!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.98,0:15:24.99,Default,,0,0,0,,How would you feel if you had to chase after them, huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.99,0:15:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I just wanted a story of camaraderie \Nbetween the paratroopers and you, ground forces! {/write about}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.57,0:15:30.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Ptui! Camaraderie?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.03,0:15:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,...with our paratroopers, that make the world envy us...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.32,0:15:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Camaraderie my ass!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.37,0:15:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Enough. {trusting HA's Stop it.}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.89,0:15:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,If you excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.08,0:15:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.13,0:15:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,But... But Ensign...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.52,0:15:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Apologize!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.22,0:15:49.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I was wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.95,0:16:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Take a look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.50,0:16:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Wreathes are abound on the paratroopers' graves.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.54,0:16:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But not a single one on the ground troops' graves.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.74,0:16:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Does that make it any clearer for you \Nas to why that soldier before cried?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.12,0:16:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I got a story{actually "I know" but what can he know?}. There was a soldier who landed \Nwith a parachute. He treated me with 5 of his cigarettes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.54,0:16:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,He was also very gentle when holding my child. \NHe was kind. A hearty soldier, however you look at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.46,0:16:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Please make sure to write my story.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.53,0:16:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,They're an intrepid bunch. \NThey need a lot of strength to handle a parachute! {actually "the parachute was strong" but he probably refers to the paratrooper by "parachute"}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.04,0:16:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,If you look at the local press, {actually "people related to the press/news"}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.97,0:17:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the paratroopers are currently the only talk of the island.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.49,0:17:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they know acting this way would delight your ilk. {VERY unsure what he means, was "Because they know you guys are happy with it." in HA}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.55,0:17:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I know it's in your nature to always pick \Nthe flashiest of stories for your job.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.25,0:17:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,However, we, ground troops also had our share of fighting.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.55,0:17:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We shed the same blood, \Ncrawled under the same bullets as our comrades.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.62,0:17:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't that make it clear to you, \Nwhere the animosity and hatred are coming from?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.94,0:17:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.96,0:17:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you lose composure again? {to act violently; to rage; to struggle; to be riotous}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.07,0:17:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, yes sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.07,0:17:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,How come the soldiers who fought conventionally \Nhave to pick a fight with paratroopers nearly every night? {I hate this line and I've no clue what he means, was "Why do soldiers who have fought soberly have to hit each other almost every night?" in HA; I can understand the first part to be a comparison of ground troops with paratroopers, but why does he say "hit each other"? why do they have no choice? why is he asking ths from a journalist???}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.08,0:18:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The guerrillas here received a professional drilling.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.74,0:18:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Make sure to take every precaution.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.59,0:18:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.44,0:18:28.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.09,0:18:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm worried about that glee of confidence in your eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.61,0:18:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You may think you're sufficiently prepared, \Nbut you shouldn't get too carried away. {/awareness/knowledge} {chasing too far; pursuing relentlessly}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.10,0:18:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The objective of your mission is not to purge \Nall the guerrillas with one big sweep,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.03,0:18:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,but instead - to wear them out with piecemeal patrols.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.35,0:18:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.08,0:18:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It's of utmost importance to decide \Nwhen to stop the pursuit.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.04,0:18:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You absolutely shouldn't chase them too deep. {/get carried away}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.46,0:19:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Ensign Murai's men were ordered by the \Nbattalion commander to go on a garrison security duty. {honestly, no clue what he means, lit is "in regards/about the defense; defence; guard; policing; security landing force" - I'd assume "the auxillary battalion, guarding the flanks of the landing party" or something like that; missing from HA}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.78,0:19:24.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Their task was handling the remnants of the Dutch troops, \Nwho kept waging a guerrilla war inland of Celebes. {/in the middle} {unsure what's "kuchi" here, like, what's an entrance to the middle?}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.48,0:19:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,One should never forget that a soldier is still a human. {no idea why he says that}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.49,0:19:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,There's some bizarre mood in the air.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.22,0:19:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Well it's the first time in a while, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.55,0:19:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.50,0:19:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,We're playing the leading role this time around! {no clue what's this shiatsu, trusting HA}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.06,0:19:53.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We will become the talk of the town after this! {/will be written about a lot}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.96,0:21:00.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The fighting that day
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.84,0:21:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,was as though the soldiers \Nwere venting the grudges of the past. {/up until now} {HA: The battle is like clearing up the past. What was hidden in the chests of the soldiers suddenly bursts out.}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.94,0:21:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,This resentment{added instead of "something/thing/mono"}, that's been secretly mounting \Nin their chests for months
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.17,0:21:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,suddenly gushed forth in one big violent stream.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.02,0:21:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,With a tremendous vigor, \Nthey fought to destroy the guerrillas for good.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.02,0:21:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We're playing the leading role this time!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.08,0:21:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Focus on the operation.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.77,0:21:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Without focusing on the operation, \Nyou can't get anything done. {no clue what he means, this fucking concept of "prioritize the sakusen" is already cryptic enough by itself; was "Is there a way to do something other than prioritize the plan?" in HA which is literal}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.77,0:21:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,No paratroopers to get in the way!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.83,0:21:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,This time, they have no choice but to write about us!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.08,0:21:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Oblivious even to the fear of death, \Nthe soldiers behaved, one might even say, way too violently. {rough; wild; rude; harsh; gruff; violent}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.18,0:21:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,They didn't know where to stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.51,0:22:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,When chasing the enemy into the woods, \Nyou can't go too deep.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.52,0:23:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,In this suppression operation, the attacking side \Nsuffered 7 casualties, including the platoon commander.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.82,0:23:07.01,Default,,0,0,0,,For a lopsided battle like that, \Nthat casualty rate was abnormally high.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.24,0:23:12.27,Default,,0,0,0,,His subordinates became forgetful of a timely decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.27,0:23:16.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Unable to contain this urge, they kept charging forward \Nruthlessly against their certain death.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.97,0:23:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What made them behave this way?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.66,0:23:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The astounding success of the Celebes{ capture} operation
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.63,0:23:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,furnished the Japanese troops with great confidence \Nin the subsequent southern operations.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.26,0:23:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet, however insignificant, this particular battle,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.37,0:23:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is bound to make us give another thought \Nto the commander's words, said prior to it:
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.96,0:23:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Focus on nothing but the operation. {/concentrate/prioritize/focus}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.68,0:24:07.63,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,0)}The Pacific War taught us the preciousness of peace.\NBut also instilled numerous lessons on how to live.{太平洋戦争はわれわれに平和の尊さを教えたがまた生きるための教訓を数多くのこしている}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.94,0:24:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,January 1942. Japanese forces occupy Manila, \Nthe ultimate target of the Philippines campaign.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.54,0:24:21.70,Default,,0,0,0,,However, Supreme Commander General MacArthur's forces, \Ncornered at the Bataan Peninsula make a counter-attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.70,0:24:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The operation suffers a setback. {setback; failure (e.g. plans, business); frustration; discouragement}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.92,0:24:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,In the enormous dark jungle, \Nthe Japanese army is suffering from starvation and malaria.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.41,0:24:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Their commander Lieutenant General Homma \Nis making a rash decision. {lit: with (mental) agony; anguish; suffering; distress}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.44,0:24:38.48,Sign,,0,0,0,,Episode 11 \NThe Fall of Bataan and Corregidor {バターン・コレヒドール攻略}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.16,0:24:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't miss the next week's decision: \NThe Fall of Bataan and Corregidor.
Comment: 0,0:24:43.11,0:24:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{ch}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.55,0:24:48.16,Default,,0,0,50,,If you're a man, let's put your strength to test{男だったら　力を試せ}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.16,0:24:52.50,Default,,0,0,50,,If you are a man, keep your hopes sizzling{男だったら　希望(のぞみ)を燃やせ}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.50,0:24:56.86,Default,,0,0,50,,If you are a man, don't lose your heart{男だったら　くじけるな}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.86,0:25:05.43,Default,,0,0,50,,Because there's just you and me, a man and a man{俺もおまえも　男と男}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.43,0:25:13.86,Default,,0,0,50,,With crimson blood flowing in our veins all the same{おなじ真赤な　血が通う}
